    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
        <h3>Scheduling a Message</h3>
        <p>The final step of the process is for the user to schedule the message. The crucial aspect in this step was to make the metadata clear and concise for the user. I wanted to make they know:
            <ul>
                <li>Who they are sending to (segments)</li>
                <li>Who is it being sent from (from:email & address)</li>
                <li>Why is being sent (subject line)</li>
                <li>What is being sent (template preview)</li>
            </ul>
        Once that data is confirmed, all they have to do is pick a send time. This will be dependent if it is a multi-channel campaign. If that is case they will have a pick a time for both email and direct mail.
        </p>
