        <h2>Concluding Thoughts</h2>
        <p>One of the main takeaways I gained from this project was learning how to be cognisant of my own biases when designing and concepting certain interactions. I found myself making certain interaction patterns that I felt were familiar, but when applying it to the end user I quickly saw that they did not match up. By forcing myself to look at every pattern and assumption through the eyes of the end user, I learned to make more human centered design choices. </p> 
        <p>This was also my first agency project which was a great learning experience on how to present to and work with a serious client. I learned from my PM to make sure that every screen that is being shown has a clear purpose. By doing so I was able to gather much more useful feedback and direction from the client. This led to a more open and creative dialogue between us.</p>
        <p>My one disappointment was the project was put on hold by the client after the MVP requirements were met. This particular project only scraped the surface of the bigger project scope. I would have really enjoyed applying my user knowledge to the more complex functionality that was scheduled for future releases.</p>
